Package: aire.zmvm
Type: Package
Title: Download pollution data for the Zona Metropolitana del Valle de Mexico
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(person("Diego", "Valle-Jones", email = "diego@diegovalle.net", role = c("aut", "cre")))
Description: The Mexico City government mantains a network of censors to
    continually monitor pollution. This package provides R functions that can
    download the daily maximum, minimum, hourly average or real-time data for each
    of the pollution measuring stations or geographic zones. It also contains the
    locations of each of the stations. See <http://aire.cdmx.gob.mx/> for the air
    pollution website.
URL: https://hoyodesmog.diegovalle.net/aire.zmvm.html, https://github.com/diegovalle/aire.zmvm
BugReports: https://github.com/diegovalle/aire.zmvm/issues
License: BSD_3_clause + file LICENSE
LazyData: TRUE
Depends:
    R (>= 2.10)
Suggests:
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    testthat,
    ggplot2
Imports:
    lubridate,
    dplyr,
    rvest,
    tidyr,
    stringr,
    xml2,
    httr,
    readr
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
